    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1882-04-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1882-04-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="58"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d58">
                <head>No. 58.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Trescot</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Special Mission of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1882-04-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 12, 1882</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Will leave on the 15th, being absent a few days, to see Montero. I believe bases
                    negotiations between the belligerents can be attained. Is most important I
                    should be in Washington, D. C., before opening of the negotiations to inform you
                    of facts. Telegraph answer Lima.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>TRESCOT.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
